      • DataDump

        public DataDump(java.io.File dir,
        Profile prof,
        boolean singleTraceDir,
        boolean overwrite)
         throws java.io.IOException
        Initializes a new instance of DataDump. If singleTraceDir is set to true, the datadump file will automatically be named and saved into the provided trace directory. No error or file chooser dialogs will be displayed and errors/exceptions will be thrown rather than shown in an error dialog. The overwrite flag is only valid when singleTraceDir is set to true.
        Parameters:
        dir - File
        prof - Profile
        singleTraceDir - boolean
        overwrite - boolean
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
